## Basic Data Retrieval

**1. View all reviews**

```sql
SELECT * FROM reviews;
```

Displays all records stored in the `reviews` table.

**2. View structure of properties table**

```sql
DESCRIBE properties;
```

Shows the columns, data types, and structure of the `properties` table.

---

## Updating Data

**3. Update property title**

```sql
UPDATE properties 
SET property_title = 'Independent House Chromepet'
WHERE property_id = 55;
```

Updates the title of the property whose ID is 55.

**4. Modify phone column in customers table**

```sql
ALTER TABLE customers
MODIFY phone VARCHAR(20);
```

Changes the data type of the `phone` column to allow up to 20 characters.

**5. Update property price**

```sql
UPDATE properties
SET price = 9000000
WHERE property_id = 2;
```

Updates the price of property with ID 2.

---

## Filtering Data

**6. Properties in Chennai**

```sql
SELECT * FROM properties
WHERE city = 'Chennai';
```

Retrieves all properties located in Chennai.

**7. Properties above a certain price**

```sql
SELECT * FROM properties
WHERE price > 10000000;
```

Displays properties priced above 10,000,000.

---

## Aggregate Functions

**8. Highest property price**

```sql
SELECT MAX(price) AS highest_price
FROM properties;
```

Finds the most expensive property in the database.

**9. Lowest rental property price**

```sql
SELECT MIN(price) AS lowest_price
FROM properties
WHERE listing_type = 'Rent';
```

Finds the lowest rental price among properties listed for rent.

---

## Grouping Data

**10. Count properties by city**

```sql
SELECT city, COUNT(*) AS total
FROM properties
GROUP BY city;
```

Counts how many properties exist in each city.

---

## Join Queries

**11. Customer transactions**

```sql
SELECT t.transaction_id, c.customer_name, t.transaction_amount
FROM transactions t
JOIN customers c
ON t.customer_id = c.customer_id;
```

Shows transaction details along with the customer name.

**12. Property transaction details**

```sql
SELECT p.property_title, c.customer_name, a.agent_name, t.transaction_amount
FROM transactions t
JOIN properties p ON t.property_id = p.property_id
JOIN customers c ON t.customer_id = c.customer_id
JOIN agents a ON t.agent_id = a.agent_id;
```

Displays property, customer, agent, and transaction amount for each deal.

---

## Subqueries

**13. Most expensive property**

```sql
SELECT * 
FROM properties
WHERE price = (SELECT MAX(price) FROM properties);
```

Finds the property with the highest price.

**14. Customers with high-value transactions**

```sql
SELECT customer_name
FROM customers
WHERE customer_id IN (
SELECT customer_id
FROM transactions
WHERE transaction_amount > 10000000
);
```

Shows customers who made transactions above 10,000,000.

---

## Analytical Queries

**15. Total revenue from sales**

```sql
SELECT SUM(transaction_amount) AS total_revenue
FROM transactions
WHERE transaction_type = 'Sale';
```

Calculates the total revenue from property sales.

**16. Agent with most deals**

```sql
SELECT agent_id, COUNT(*) AS total_deals
FROM transactions
GROUP BY agent_id
ORDER BY total_deals DESC
LIMIT 1;
```

Finds the agent who completed the highest number of transactions.

**17. Properties with more than three amenities**

```sql
SELECT property_id, COUNT(amenity_id) AS amenity_count
FROM property_amenities
GROUP BY property_id
HAVING COUNT(amenity_id) > 3;
```

Lists properties that have more than three amenities.

---

## Properties Without Related Data

**18. Properties without visits**

```sql
SELECT property_id, property_title
FROM properties
WHERE property_id NOT IN (SELECT property_id FROM visits);
```

Finds properties that have never been visited by customers.

---

## Conditional Queries

**19. Categorize properties by price**

```sql
SELECT property_title, price,
CASE
WHEN price >= 20000000 THEN 'Premium'
WHEN price >= 10000000 THEN 'Mid-Range'
ELSE 'Budget'
END AS price_category
FROM properties;
```

Classifies properties into price categories.

**20. Region classification**

```sql
SELECT property_title, city,
CASE
WHEN city = 'Chennai' THEN 'Tamil Nadu Region'
ELSE 'Other State'
END AS region_type
FROM properties
ORDER BY city;
```

Labels properties based on location.

**21. Property value classification**

```sql
SELECT property_title, price,
IF(price > 10000000, 'High Value', 'Normal Value') AS value_type
FROM properties;
```

Categorizes properties based on price value.

---

## Join Types

**22. Left Join – Properties and owners**

```sql
SELECT p.property_title, o.owner_name
FROM properties p
LEFT JOIN owners o
ON p.owner_id = o.owner_id;
```

Shows all properties and their owners, including properties without an owner.

**23. Properties with multiple transactions**

```sql
SELECT p.property_title, COUNT(t.transaction_id) AS total_transactions
FROM properties p
LEFT JOIN transactions t
ON p.property_id = t.property_id
GROUP BY p.property_id
HAVING COUNT(t.transaction_id) > 1;
```

Finds properties involved in more than one transaction.

**24. Right Join – Agents without transactions**

```sql
SELECT a.agent_name
FROM transactions t
RIGHT JOIN agents a
ON t.agent_id = a.agent_id
WHERE t.transaction_id IS NULL;
```

Lists agents who have not handled any transactions.

**25. Cross Join – Customers and agents**

```sql
SELECT c.customer_name, a.agent_name
FROM customers c
CROSS JOIN agents a
ORDER BY a.agent_name;
```

Creates all possible combinations of customers and agents.

---

## Additional Subqueries

**26. Properties with reviews**

```sql
SELECT property_title
FROM properties
WHERE property_id IN (
SELECT property_id
FROM reviews
);
```

Finds properties that have received reviews.

**27. Unsold properties**

```sql
SELECT property_title
FROM properties
WHERE property_id NOT IN (
SELECT property_id
FROM transactions
WHERE transaction_type = 'Sale'
);
```

Lists properties that have not been sold.

**28. Active agents**

```sql
SELECT agent_name
FROM agents
WHERE agent_id IN (
SELECT agent_id
FROM transactions
GROUP BY agent_id
HAVING COUNT(*) > 2
);
```

Finds agents who have handled more than two transactions.

**29. Properties priced above city average**

```sql
SELECT property_title, city, price
FROM properties p
WHERE price > (
SELECT AVG(price)
FROM properties
WHERE city = p.city
);
```

Displays properties priced above the average price in their city.

---

## Data Deletion Operations

**30. Delete old visits**

```sql
DELETE FROM visits
WHERE visit_date < '2025-01-01';
```

Removes visit records before January 1, 2025.

**31. Remove all visit records**

```sql
TRUNCATE TABLE visits;
```

Deletes all records from the `visits` table quickly.

**32. Remove reviews table**

```sql
DROP TABLE reviews;
```

Permanently deletes the `reviews` table from the database.
